# Progress Notes Rule

## Location

- Save progress notes in `docs/progress/`.
- Keep one file per session using `YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md`.

## When to add notes

- Add a brief note after substantial code or config changes.
- Add a note any time the user explicitly requests one.
- Skip notes for trivial reads, quick answers, or no-op changes.

## What to include

Keep entries concise and outcome-focused:

- Objective
- Scope (key files)
- Changes
- Validation (only commands actually run)
- Risks or blockers
- Next actions

## Current project context

- Most recent note: `docs/progress/2026-04-14-photo-enabled-markers.md`.
- Recent work includes:
  - map marker hover previews with multi-photo support (`phototab`)
  - single-photo fallback rendering without tabs
  - dynamic location detail page route and per-photo metadata display
  - CMS-ready location records with `photographer`, `photoDate`, `direction`, `comments?`
- Validation entries should record command outcomes exactly (for example, missing script vs passing build), not inferred success.

## Style

- Prefer 3-8 bullets total.
- Capture decisions and outcomes, not step-by-step narration.
